        public static boolean isPrime(int testNum)
        Returns whether or not a given integer is a prime number.
        Parameters:
        testNum - The number that will be tested to be prime.
        Returns:
        A boolean value. True if testNum is prime. False otherwise

      • primes

        public static int[] primes(int primesToCreate)
        Returns an integer array which contains the requested number of primes. Starting at index 0, the array length will match the number of requested primes.
        Parameters:
        primesToCreate - An integer containing the number of primes to calculate
        Returns:

      • primesLessThan

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> primesLessThan(int endPoint)
        Generate all of the prime numbers below a given end point.

        Implemented by finding divisibility between numbers from 2 to the square root of the end point.

        Parameters:
        endPoint - An integer containing the upper bound of primes to calculate
        Returns:
        An ArrayList containing all prime integers from 3 to the upper bound

      • primesLessThanSieveRemove

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> primesLessThanSieveRemove(int endPoint)
        Generate all the prime numbers below a given end point.

        Implemented using a Sieve of Eratosthenes approach. Finds Multiples of a number, removing them from a list and keeping the original number.

        Parameters:
        endPoint - An integer containing the upper bound of primes to calculate
        Returns:
        An ArrayList containing all the prime integers from 3 to the upper bound

      • primesLessThanSieveAdd

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> primesLessThanSieveAdd(int endPoint)
        Generate all the prime numbers below a given end point.

        Implemented using reverse Sieve of Eratosthenes approach. Finds Checks a list forMultiples of a number, if none are found the number is added to the list.

        Parameters:
        endPoint - An integer containing the upper bound of primes to calculate
        Returns:
        An ArrayList containing all the prime integers from 3 to the upper bound
